						<summary>

						<p>On the north base of the Karivaradarāja-perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kōṉēriṉmaikoṇḍāṉ—Vīranārayaṇa (?) c. (1139-49 A.D.).</hi></p>						

						<p>This badly damaged inscription records the gift of paddy for offerings to the god Karimāṇikkāḻvār at Kumaraṅgabhīma-chchaturvēdimaṅgalam by the king.</p>						

